<exercise id="eip-548"><problem id="eip-394">
  <para id="eip-968">CO<sub>2</sub> absorbs with a peak wavelength of 4260 nm in the IR. Suppose a standard gas sample held at 1000.0 kPa with a CO<sub>2</sub> partial pressure of 100.00 kPa has an absorbance of 0.30 when at 4260 nm when measured by an NDIR instrument. What would be the maximum absorbance at 4260 nm of a sample collected from a car’s exhaust (and measured by the same NDIR instrument) at 1.00 atm than could indicate compliance with the EU’s maximum of 130 g of CO<sub>2</sub> emitted per km traveled? The car emits a total of 6500.0 L from its exhaust each kilometer it travels. Assume that CO<sub>2</sub> is the only species in either sample absorbing at 4260 nm, and that when [CO<sub>2</sub>] = 0, absorbance at 4260 nm is equal to 0. Assume temperature of 0 °C and ideal gas behavior for all gases.</para>
</problem>

<solution id="eip-108">
  <para id="eip-88">Begin by using the given partial pressures to calculate the mole fraction of CO<sub>2</sub>.</para>
<equation id="eip-545"><m:math display="block">
            <m:semantics>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>χ</m:mi>
                  <m:msub>
                    <m:mi>o</m:mi>
                    <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                  </m:msub>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                <m:mfrac>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>100</m:mn>
                    <m:mi mathvariant="italic">kPa</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>1000</m:mn>
                    <m:mi mathvariant="italic">kPa</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mfrac>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>0.1</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">{χ} rsub {{o} rsub {2}} = {100 kPa} over {1000 kPa} =0.1</m:annotation>
            </m:semantics>
          </m:math>
        </equation><para id="import-auto-idm699901904">0.1 mole fraction means that in 1 L of gas, 0.1 L is CO<sub>2</sub>.</para>
        
        <equation id="eip-666"><m:math display="block">
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mfrac>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>0.1</m:mn>
                  <m:mi>L</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>22.4</m:mn>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mi>L</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">/</m:mo>
                    <m:mi mathvariant="italic">mol</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mfrac>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
              <m:mn>0.00446428571</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mtext/>
            <m:mtext>mol</m:mtext>
            <m:mtext/>
            <m:msub>
              <m:mtext>CO</m:mtext>
              <m:mtext>2</m:mtext>
            </m:msub>
            <m:mtext> in 1 L of exhaust</m:mtext>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">{0.1 L} over {22.4 L/mol} = 0.00446428571 " "  "mol"  " " {"CO"} rsub {"2"} " in 1 L of exhaust"</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </equation><para id="import-auto-idm453743088">The standard is then determined to be 0.004464 M CO<sub>2</sub>.</para>
        
        <equation id="eip-38"><m:math display="block">
            <m:semantics>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>A</m:mi>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>0.300</m:mn>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                  <m:mi mathvariant="italic">εb</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">[</m:mo>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:msub>
                        <m:mi mathvariant="italic">CO</m:mi>
                        <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                      </m:msub>
                    </m:mrow>
                    <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">]</m:mo>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                  <m:mi mathvariant="italic">εb</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">[</m:mo>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>0.0044642871</m:mn>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">]</m:mo>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">A=0.300=εb left [{CO} rsub {2} right ] =εb left [0.0044642871 right ]</m:annotation>
            </m:semantics>
          </m:math>
        </equation><para id="import-auto-idm495190704">Solve for the product εb in Beer-Lambert’s law.</para>
        
        <equation id="eip-151"><m:math display="block">
            <m:semantics>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi mathvariant="italic">εb</m:mi>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>64.199979</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:msup>
                  <m:mi mathvariant="italic">mol</m:mi>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                    <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:msup>
                <m:mi>L</m:mi>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">εb=64.199979  {mol} ^ {-1}  L</m:annotation>
            </m:semantics>
          </m:math>
        </equation><para id="import-auto-idm310093728">Calculate allowable moles of 130 g to be emitted in 1 km.</para>
        
        <equation id="eip-415"><m:math display="block">
            <m:semantics>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mtext/>
                <m:mfrac>
                  <m:mtext>130 g allowed</m:mtext>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mtext>44.01 g C</m:mtext>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mtext>O</m:mtext>
                      <m:mtext>2</m:mtext>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mtext>/</m:mtext>
                    <m:mtext>mol</m:mtext>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mfrac>
                <m:mtext>=2.953874 </m:mtext>
                <m:mtext>mol</m:mtext>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mtext>CO</m:mtext>
                  <m:mtext>2</m:mtext>
                </m:msub>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">" " {"130 g allowed"} over {"44.01 g C" {"O"} rsub {"2"} "/"  "mol" } "=2.953874 "  "mol"    {"CO"} rsub {"2"}</m:annotation>
            </m:semantics>
          </m:math>
        </equation><para id="import-auto-idm340672496">Calculate the maximum allowable concentration (molarity) of CO<sub>2 </sub>in the exhaust.</para>
        
        <equation id="eip-913"><m:math display="block">
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:msub>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:msub>
                    <m:mtext>[CO</m:mtext>
                    <m:mtext>2</m:mtext>
                  </m:msub>
                  <m:mtext>]</m:mtext>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mi mathvariant="italic">max</m:mi>
              </m:msub>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
              <m:mfrac>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>2.95</m:mn>
                  <m:mi mathvariant="italic">mol</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>6500</m:mn>
                  <m:mi>L</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mfrac>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
              <m:mn>0.0045444</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mi>M</m:mi>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">{{"[CO"} rsub {"2"} "]"} rsub {max} = {2.95 mol} over {6500 L} =0.0045444 M</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </equation><para id="import-auto-idm376587008">Use this concentration (molarity) and εb to calculate the maximum allowed absorbance.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm376586752"><m:math display="block">
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:msub>
              <m:mtext>A</m:mtext>
              <m:mtext>max </m:mtext>
            </m:msub>
            <m:mtext>= (</m:mtext>
            <m:mtext>εb</m:mtext>
            <m:mtext>)</m:mtext>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:msub>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:msub>
                    <m:mtext>[CO</m:mtext>
                    <m:mtext>2</m:mtext>
                  </m:msub>
                  <m:mtext>]</m:mtext>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mtext>max</m:mtext>
              </m:msub>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>64.199979</m:mn>
                    <m:mfrac>
                      <m:mi>L</m:mi>
                      <m:mi mathvariant="italic">mol</m:mi>
                    </m:mfrac>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>0.0045444</m:mn>
                    <m:mfrac>
                      <m:mi mathvariant="italic">mol</m:mi>
                      <m:mi>L</m:mi>
                    </m:mfrac>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
              <m:mn>0.29175038</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">{"A"} rsub {"max "} "= ("  "εb"  ")" {{"[CO"} rsub {"2"} "]"} rsub {"max"} =(64.199979  {L} over {mol}  )(0.0045444 {mol} over {L} )= 0.29175038</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm623784800">The final answer should be expressed as 0.292, conserving three significant figures.</para>
</solution>
